b'[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe01060.htm)  [Next](sbe01062.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/B002DEMBW6/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n[![](../../img/tn_hin.jpg)](index.htm)  \n_The Upanishads, Part 1 (SBE01)_ , by Max Muller, [1879], at sacred-texts.com\n\n* * *\n\n### THIRD KHA _N_ _D_ A.\n\n1\\. The western rays of the sun are the honey-cells behind. The Saman verses\nare the bees, the Sama-veda sacrifice is the flower, the water is the nectar.\n\n2\\. Those very Saman verses (as bees) brooded over the Sama-veda sacrifice;\nand from it, thus brooded on, sprang as its (nectar) essence, fame, glory of\ncountenance, vigour, strength, and health.\n\n3\\. That flowed forth and went towards the sun. And that forms what we call\nthe dark (k _ri_ sh _n_ a) light of the sun.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: III, 4](sbe01062.htm)\n\n'